        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 24 at 6:22PM CDT until August 24 at 7:15PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>SVRAMA

The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Lipscomb County in the Panhandle of Texas...
Northeastern Hemphill County in the Panhandle of Texas...

* Until 715 PM CDT.

* At 622 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Higgins, or
13 miles southeast of Lipscomb, moving south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
Hail damage to vehicles is expected.

* Locations impacted include...
Higgins.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
